criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Be male or female between the ages of 18 and 60 inclusive;

          -  Be lightly pigmented (Fitzpatrick Skin Type I, II, III);

          -  Have read and signed the written Informed Consent Form and have completed a HIPAA
             Authorization Form in conformance with 45CFR Parts 160 and 164;

          -  Be in general good health as determined by the subject's medical history and in the
             discretion of the investigator.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Have a visible sunburn;

          -  Have a history of sun hypersensitivity/photosensitivity or photosensitive dermatoses;

          -  Must not have a known sensitivity or allergy against any of the active and non-active
             ingredients of the test product.

          -  Have a history of allergies or sensitivities to cosmetics, toiletries or any
             dermatological products.
